    <h1>📚 Psychology & Mental Health Resources</h1>
    <p>A curated list of the best resources in psychology and mental health, covering books, research papers, websites, apps, platforms, and more.</p>
    <hr>

    <h2>📚 Best Books</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/63697.The_Man_Who_Mistook_His_Wife_for_a_Hat_and_Other_Clinical_Tales">The Man Who Mistook His Wife for a Hat – Oliver Sacks</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11468377-thinking-fast-and-slow">Thinking, Fast and Slow – Daniel Kahneman</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18693771-the-body-keeps-the-score">The Body Keeps the Score – Bessel van der Kolk</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34921573-lost-connections">Lost Connections – Johann Hari</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/41881472-the-psychology-of-money">The Psychology of Money – Morgan Housel</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/66354.Flow">Flow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience – Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/56627.Stumbling_on_Happiness">Stumbling on Happiness – Daniel Gilbert</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27213329-grit">Grit: The Power of Passion and Perseverance – Angela Duckworth</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/359194.The_Lucifer_Effect">The Lucifer Effect: Understanding How Good People Turn Evil – Philip Zimbardo</a></li>
    </ul>

